1
00:00:06,960 --> 00:00:09,119
<i>Previously on "The Magicians"...</i>

2
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:10,459
There's too much magic.

3
00:00:10,460 --> 00:00:12,459
Everything that I touch just...

4
00:00:12,460 --> 00:00:14,055
it grows like crazy.

5
00:00:14,056 --> 00:00:15,839
I'm gonna let your bullshit slide

6
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:17,839
on account of you so
recently being possessed

7
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:19,879
by a homicidal monster.

8
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:21,339
<i>There was a blood worm scare,</i>

9
00:00:21,340 --> 00:00:23,147
so the Library gave a lot
of hedges the Reed's Mark.

10
00:00:23,148 --> 00:00:25,775
<i>I found a spell to remove
the Marks in a Depository.</i>

11
00:00:25,776 --> 00:00:28,319
I get you're on a mission.
One of you's got to jet.

12
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:30,446
Either one of you can hang for eternity.

13
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:32,989
I've earned the right to step off.

14
00:00:32,990 --> 00:00:34,909
We're here to study with Mayakovsky.

15
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:36,786
I hate all of you.

16
00:00:36,787 --> 00:00:37,830
Professor?

17
00:00:38,690 --> 00:00:39,770
_

18
00:00:40,249 --> 00:00:41,999
"Best bitches."

19
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,044
Wear this, and you'll see what I see.

20
00:00:44,045 --> 00:00:46,529
I'm Clarion, the goddess of melody.

21
00:00:46,530 --> 00:00:49,199
The way that you're imagining
the Harmonic Convergence

22
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,439
isn't quite enough.

23
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:53,511
<i>When all the spells cast by
all the Magicians go haywire,</i>

24
00:00:53,512 --> 00:00:56,556
<i>you're gonna get earthquakes,
starvation, plague.</i>

25
00:00:56,557 --> 00:00:58,600
She didn't have time to be delicate.

26
00:00:58,601 --> 00:01:00,476
You can't travel anymore.

27
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:02,604
What exactly are we looking for, sir?

28
00:01:02,605 --> 00:01:05,059
Not what. Who.

29
00:01:05,060 --> 00:01:07,499
- You two know each other?
- No.

30
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,279
Well, your subjects
are rightly grateful.

31
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:10,329
For sending that letter?

32
00:01:10,330 --> 00:01:12,655
AKA that thing I totally
didn't do; you did.

33
00:01:12,656 --> 00:01:15,032
I was gonna let you die for Fillory.

34
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:16,784
The Convergence can be stopped.

35
00:01:16,785 --> 00:01:20,809
All you have to do is move...

36
00:01:20,810 --> 00:01:22,041
that.

37
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:26,479
The Harmonic Convergence.

38
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:30,319
- AKA the end of the world.
- Not necessarily.

39
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:32,779
This constellation forms a cosmic sigil

40
00:01:32,780 --> 00:01:34,880
that increases magical intensity.

41
00:01:34,887 --> 00:01:37,472
It has happened in the past
without causing an apocalypse.

42
00:01:37,473 --> 00:01:39,223
But now there's surges of magic.

43
00:01:39,224 --> 00:01:42,477
So we get the disaster movie
Clarion was talking about.

44
00:01:42,478 --> 00:01:45,813
The Convergence will only occur
during this perfect alignment.

45
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:48,559
If we move the moon out of position...

46
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,519
No Convergence, no Circumstance,

47
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,620
no apocalypse.

48
00:01:51,630 --> 00:01:55,579
The moon is not just a rock in space.
It has certain properties.

49
00:01:55,580 --> 00:01:57,492
- Like?
- Magic doesn't work on it.

50
00:01:57,493 --> 00:01:59,949
Thanks to Magicians
casting haphazardly on it

51
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:02,349
for millennia, the moon is
now covered by a crust

52
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:04,519
of spell debris, blocking new spells.

53
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:07,544
If we move any piece out
of place, no Convergence.

54
00:02:07,545 --> 00:02:09,940
Well, what if we just moved Mars?

55
00:02:09,950 --> 00:02:12,423
She said with a straight face.

56
00:02:12,424 --> 00:02:14,801
The other pieces are planets.

57
00:02:14,802 --> 00:02:16,829
We can't move them
because they are, well,

58
00:02:16,830 --> 00:02:18,640
very big and far away.

59
00:02:18,650 --> 00:02:20,279
The moon is the only celestial body

60
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,599
we stand a chance of affecting.

61
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,849
But won't that screw
with the Circumstances?

62
00:02:23,850 --> 00:02:25,353
What will magic be like when we're done?

63
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:26,809
Impossible to know.

64
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:29,358
It will be a brand-new Circumstance.

65
00:02:30,010 --> 00:02:33,279
But to get to that problem,
we need to solve this one.

66
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,979
Good, well, I hope you have some ideas,

67
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:36,198
because we're striking out.

68
00:02:36,199 --> 00:02:38,701
I do. Consult the Lunatics.

69
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:42,412
- The lunatics?
- Short for "Lunar Fanatics."

70
00:02:42,413 --> 00:02:45,299
In the Middle Ages,
people thought insanity

71
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:47,339
was caused by changing
phases of the moon.

72
00:02:47,340 --> 00:02:50,378
In fact, it was often a Lunatic
in the throes of worship.

73
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:53,499
They claimed to be able to
achieve a magical connection

74
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:56,139
with the moon and even under
some circumstances...

75
00:02:56,140 --> 00:02:57,169
move it.

76
00:02:57,170 --> 00:02:58,679
Well, that sounds useful.

77
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:01,579
- Mm.
- Well, if it's just branding,

78
00:03:01,580 --> 00:03:03,267
it means they're not
really crazy, right?

79
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:06,359
My dad always said that
they were batshit insane,

80
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:08,799
and he married my mom,
so he had a pretty high bar

81
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,919
for mental instability.

82
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:13,379
Regardless, they know more
about the moon than anyone.

83
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:16,859
I believe that talking to them
is our only chance at success.

84
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:19,824
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

85
00:03:19,825 --> 00:03:22,869
<i>[EERIE MUSIC]</i>

86
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:24,829
<i>♪</i>

87
