88
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,679
_

89
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,966
<i>What people don't understand</i>

90
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:38,819
is there is a skeleton of the universe,

91
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:40,079
but we are the bones.

92
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:42,399
Oh, that's good to know.

93
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,679
I am a humerus.

94
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:46,139
You? Patella.

95
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:48,679
We wanted to ask you about the moon.

96
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:50,279
Can we talk about it?

97
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:53,279
It... it?

98
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,027
Her Lunacy...

99
00:03:56,320 --> 00:04:00,099
Identifies as she/her.

100
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,739
That's right. We knew that, right?

101
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:04,769
- Of course.
- We know.

102
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:07,663
If we wanted to move Her,
how could we do that?

103
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:10,149
You don't move Her.

104
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:12,649
Okay, listen, Reba.

105
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:15,585
In just a few days, a whole lot
of people are going to die.

106
00:04:15,586 --> 00:04:16,799
That's a whole lot people

107
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,382
that will never get to worship the moon.

108
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:20,959
They will never get to
know Her like you do.

109
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:24,689
If She can help us save
all of those lives...

110
00:04:24,690 --> 00:04:27,259
imagine everyone that will realize

111
00:04:27,260 --> 00:04:29,629
just how much She deserves their love,

112
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:30,978
their reverence.

113
00:04:30,979 --> 00:04:32,689
So will you help us?

114
00:04:34,770 --> 00:04:36,790
Just to be clear.

115
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:40,279
You don't move Her.

116
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,615
You ask Her to move.

117
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:46,035
And She won't let you speak to
Her unless you get moon brain.

118
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:47,912
So one of us needs moon brain.

119
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:50,949
Not one of you. Three of you.

120
00:04:50,950 --> 00:04:53,699
A single Magician cannot
generate enough power

121
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:54,870
to reach Her.

122
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:56,629
So it's a cooperative spell then.

123
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,756
It is a sign of respect, Kneecap,

124
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:01,384
that allows you to see
Her as She truly is.

125
00:05:01,385 --> 00:05:04,229
If you have moon brain,
then you will see Her aura.

126
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:06,419
Now it is red, but when you
perform the Dianic Ritual,

127
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:07,430
Her aura will change.

128
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:09,329
If it is yellow, She is considering.

129
00:05:09,330 --> 00:05:11,679
If it is green, She is listening.

130
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:15,709
Only then may you ask Her

131
00:05:15,710 --> 00:05:16,949
to move.

132
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,239
Red, yellow, green.

133
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,519
The guy who invented the stoplight,

134
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,400
was he a Lunatic too?

135
00:05:22,406 --> 00:05:24,899
William Potts? Yeah.

136
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,679
Oh, cool.

137
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:29,119
All three Magicians
must perform the ritual

138
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,589
until the moon is listening.

139
00:05:31,590 --> 00:05:35,159
A warning: once Her aura is green,
She may choose to listen

140
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:37,503
to anyone who calls to Her, so be ready.

141
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:40,004
You must choose one,
the strongest among you,

142
00:05:40,005 --> 00:05:42,843
to speak to Her, like the
old Lunatics taught us to.

143
00:05:44,094 --> 00:05:45,679
For this second part,
however, there is a price.

144
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:49,680
- A price, like blood?
- It is like blood to Her.

145
00:05:49,690 --> 00:05:52,810
You will need a piece
of Her. A sacrifice.

146
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:54,779
A piece?

147
00:05:54,780 --> 00:05:56,981
- Or like a moon rock?
- Yes.

148
00:05:56,982 --> 00:05:59,259
But be aware,

149
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:01,289
this will destroy it,

150
00:06:01,290 --> 00:06:03,989
so don't use your favorite one.

151
00:06:05,157 --> 00:06:07,617
This is the price of
speaking to the moon.

152
00:06:07,618 --> 00:06:09,744
Just a few more questions.

153
00:06:09,745 --> 00:06:12,999
What is moon brain,
and how do we get it?

154
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,083
- Everyone line up.
- Pudding time!

155
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:18,127
Lovely to speak to you.

156
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:20,046
You too, Kneecap. [CLICKS TONGUE]

157
00:06:20,047 --> 00:06:23,109
<i>[FUNKY MUSIC]</i>

158
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:25,049
<i>♪</i>

159
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:28,540
You ever just spin a globe,
stick your finger down,

160
00:06:28,550 --> 00:06:30,719
see where it lands?

161
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,059
It's almost always water,

162
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:33,379
because, well, duh.

163
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:36,789
Earth is mostly water, but
sometimes it's the Sahara,

164
00:06:36,790 --> 00:06:39,649
sometimes the Urals.

165
00:06:39,650 --> 00:06:42,652
That's what you'd be doing
if you tried to travel.

166
00:06:42,653 --> 00:06:45,863
Only instead of the
globe, the multiverse,

167
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:48,739
which is bigger and deadlier.

168
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:50,239
Afraid you'd say that.

169
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,879
I looked at everything I could think of,

170
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,599
magical and medical.

171
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,582
Nada. You're grounded.

172
00:06:56,959 --> 00:06:58,579
All right, well, since
I ain't traveling,

173
00:06:58,580 --> 00:06:59,749
I should probably step down.

174
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,299
Uh, if you're offering your resignation,

175
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:02,309
I don't accept.

176
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:04,089
Not offering. Stating.

177
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:06,217
With Dean Fogg out indefinitely,

178
00:07:06,218 --> 00:07:09,137
Brakebills has instituted our
Dean Vanishment Protocol.

179
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:11,989
Of course, that's a thing here.

180
00:07:11,990 --> 00:07:14,329
Yeah, and uh... [CLEARS THROAT]

181
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,851
That makes me acting Dean Lipson.

182
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,269
There's no instruction manual,

183
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,969
so I'm kinda dean-ing on the fly here,

184
00:07:18,970 --> 00:07:20,099
but one thing I do know

185
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:22,499
is losing a professor who was disabled

186
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,020
on school grounds ain't happening.

187
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:26,579
I mean, the optics would
be pure shitflakes.

188
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:30,450
So your contract will be
honored and enforced.

189
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:33,740
Oh, also.

190
00:07:35,380 --> 00:07:36,915
We need a new Welters coach.

191
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:42,789
I've been on the inside,
and I'm telling you

192
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:44,335
it's a goddamn goose-stepping,

193
00:07:44,336 --> 00:07:47,091
fairy-snatching, ethnic
cleansing Gestapo.

194
00:07:47,092 --> 00:07:49,299
To be fair, the ethnic
cleansing happened

195
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:51,220
after the Dark King left, so...

196
00:07:51,221 --> 00:07:53,181
He's innocent because he delegates?

197
00:07:53,182 --> 00:07:54,719
No, that's not what I'm saying.

198
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:57,099
Someone in this castle ordered
the hunt on that Fairy.

199
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:58,439
It could have been the Dark King,

200
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,839
but if it was someone else,

201
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,647
killing Seb might just
make things worse.

202
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:06,862
So we have to find out
who before we... coup.

203
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:10,990
I just wanna stab someone.

204
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:13,289
I haven't heard you
this bloodthirsty in...

205
00:08:13,290 --> 00:08:15,786
well, not that long,
but still, it's notable.

206
00:08:15,787 --> 00:08:18,329
Maybe I'm a bit on edge.

207
00:08:18,330 --> 00:08:20,207
Josh keeps wanting to talk.

208
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,399
You mean about how you wanted

209
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,499
to leave him in the past to die?

210
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:23,920
Yeah, that.

211
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:27,139
So far, I'm doing a good
job of avoiding him,

212
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:28,799
but eventually he's gonna sneak...

213
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,009
Guys.

214
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:32,579
- Hey, what's up?
- 'Sup?

215
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:34,009
First off, kudos on the hiding spot.

216
00:08:34,010 --> 00:08:35,223
It took me forever to find you.

217
00:08:35,224 --> 00:08:36,640
Pretty busy here, Josh.

218
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:37,649
You're busy?

219
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:38,851
I just got promoted to head chef.

220
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:41,049
- Oh, congratulations.
- Thank you.

221
00:08:41,050 --> 00:08:42,979
But I'm about to bail on a state dinner

222
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:45,519
and leave it to my incompetent
sous-chef because...

223
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,389
Apocalypse! Now!

224
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:49,299
Josh, would you just give it up?

225
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:50,988
He keeps trying to get us
to join his film club,

226
00:08:50,989 --> 00:08:52,698
which I told him would
never work on a planet

227
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:54,742
with no electricity or taste.

228
00:08:54,743 --> 00:08:57,995
Uh, no, uh, sorry.
This one's just a little shy.

229
00:08:57,996 --> 00:08:59,439
It... it's okay, buddy.

230
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:02,959
- Help us stop the...
- Apocalypse! Now!

231
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:06,260
- Oh.
- We need to get back to Earth.

232
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:07,839
Margo, our talk will have to wait

233
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:09,509
till after we save the world.

234
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:11,719
Oh, but then I have my
nephew's bar mitzvah.

235
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,345
So after that?

236
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:16,180
- Mazel.
- Thanks.

237
00:09:16,181 --> 00:09:18,289
[SIGHS]

238
00:09:18,290 --> 00:09:21,449
What about our thing? We have
a lot of fact-finding to do

239
00:09:21,450 --> 00:09:23,104
before I can get to stabbing.

240
00:09:23,105 --> 00:09:24,559
No problem.

241
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,273
I know just who to handle it.

242
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:28,025
<i>You want me to what?</i>

243
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:31,329
Just find out who in the
castle hates Fairies.

244
00:09:31,330 --> 00:09:33,569
Okay? And what they're doing to them.

245
00:09:33,570 --> 00:09:35,282
And why Fairies in the first place?

246
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:38,199
And maybe talk to some Fairies,
get their side of things.

247
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,479
- Okay.
- And while you're at it...

248
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,207
anything else that seems important.

249
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:44,119
Okay, okay, okay.

250
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:46,590
No, um... That seems like a
lot of open-ended questions.

251
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,599
- Mm-hmm.
- I got this maid job

252
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,699
to be close to you guys,

253
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:52,239
and now you're deserting me? [CHUCKLES]

254
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:54,636
I want to stop an apocalypse too.

255
00:09:55,780 --> 00:09:57,819
Every apocalypse-stopping mission

256
00:09:57,820 --> 00:09:59,849
